track_notes:
Mount Idaho is a difficult and very strenuous climb.

Idaho doesnt get climbed much. As a result, the trail is difficult to follow all the way up. It fades in and out. And there is a lot of loose stuff to wade through on the upper mountain. Following the route on the upper mountain is very difficult, even with a GPS route.

I have a hard time recommending this mountain because it is steep and loose and a bit dangerous. And it is very difficult to find the route (Borah is a nicer climb). But if you are into this sort of peak, it is an adventure.

My track up follows the standard route: I got off route many times. My track down takes a different route. I started scree surfing and got below my uptrack. Then I traversed back to my uptrack. Once I got to the saddle, I decided to try the scree surfing route that goes directly to the valley; it helps you quickly drop 1000 feet. But there are a few cliff bands to navigate around. Or just follow the uptrack down.
track_title: Mount Idaho - A Difficult Adventure Climb

track_notes: This is the standard route up Mount Idaho. I followed this route up. Note that even though the map shows a trail to the summit, it is not a trail really, but a use trail that fades in and out. Be prepared for a lot of difficult hiking.
